ass_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["An entity profile is a collection of entity references.\n\nThere are particularities of entity profiles depending on the entity\nresolution model being used:\n\n* **entity matching**: pairs of entity references\n* **algebraic model**: a non-empty set of entity references"]}], "exports": []}, {"name": "matchescu.typing._data", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "matchescu.typing._data.T", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "matchescu.typing._data.Record", "bases": ["Sized", "Iterable", "Protocol"], "methods": [{"name": "matchescu.typing._data.Record.__getitem__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "item", "type": {"name": "Union", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Union", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "Any", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Any", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Record values may be accessed by name or index."]}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["A `protocol <https://peps.python.org/pep-0544/>`_ for data records.\n\nA record is information structured using attributes. A record has a length\n(or size), it can be iterated over so that we can browse all of its\nattributes and each attribute may be accessed using a name or an integer\nindex."]}, {"name": "matchescu.typing._data.DataSource", "bases": ["Sized", "Protocol"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "matchescu.typing._data.DataSource.name", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "matchescu.typing._data.DataSource.traits", "type": {"name": "Iterable", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Iterable", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "Trait", "xref": {"fqname": "matchescu.typing._callable.Trait", "project": null}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["A data source is an iterable sequence of relatively similar items.\n\nData sources have a size or at least can estimate their own size. Each data\nsource has a name.\n\nAttributes\n----------\n:name str: name of the data source\n:traits Iterable[Trait]: feature extraction traits that are specific to the\n    data source."]}], "exports": []}, {"name": "matchescu.adt", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "matchescu.common.partitioning", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "matchescu.common.partitioning.compute_partition", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "all_references", "type": {"name": "list", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.list", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "equivalence", "type": {"name": "list", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.list", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "tuple", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.tuple", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "list", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.list", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "list", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.list", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "tuple", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.tuple", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}]}, "documentation": ["Partition an input set according to an equivalence relation.\n\nThe algorithm uses the Union-Find or DFU data structure.\n\n```\nparam all_references\n\nall entity references that make up the input domain\n\nparam equivalence\n\npairs that define which items are equivalent to other items\n\nreturn\n\na list of lists of tuples, where:\n```\n\n- each tuple is an entity reference\n- tuples are grouped in clusters which are represented as lists\n- the final result is a list of clusters\n"]}], "variables": [{"name": "matchescu.common.partitioning.T", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "matchescu.common.partitioning.EquivalenceClassPartitioner", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "matchescu.common.partitioning.EquivalenceClassPartitioner.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "items", "type": {"name": "list", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.list", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "T", "xref": {"fqname": "T", "project": null}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "matchescu.common.partitioning.EquivalenceClassPartitioner._find", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "x", "type": {"name": "T", "xref": {"fqname": "T", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "T", "xref": {"fqname": "T", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "matchescu.common.partitioning.EquivalenceClassPartitioner._union", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "x", "type": {"name": "T", "xref": {"fqname": "T", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "y", "type": {"name": "T", "xref": {"fqname": "T", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "matchescu.common.partitioning.EquivalenceClassPartitioner.__call__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "pairs", "type": {"name": "list", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.list", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "tuple", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.tuple", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "T", "xref": {"fqname": "T", "project": null}, "params": null}, {"name": "T", "xref": {"fqname": "T", "project": null}, "params": null}]}]}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "list", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.list", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "list", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.list", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "T", "xref": {"fqname": "T", "project": null}, "params": null}]}]}, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "matchescu.adt.entity_resolution_result", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "matchescu.adt.entity_resolution_result.EntityResolutionResult", "bases": [], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "matchescu.adt.entity_resolution_result.EntityResolutionResult.algebraic", "type": {"name": "list", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.list", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "list", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.list", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "tuple", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.tuple", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}]}, "documentation": ["Entity resolution result in terms of the Fellegi-Sunter probabilistic model.\n\nThe Fellegi-Sunter model is the oldest mathematical model for entity resolution. Its origins\ncan be traced back to the paper written by Ivan Fellegi and Alan Sunter:\n`A Theory for Record Linkage<https://www.tandfonline.com/doi/abs/10.1080/01621459.1969.10501049>`_."]}, {"name": "matchescu.adt.entity_resolution_result.EntityResolutionResult.fsm", "type": {"name": "list", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.list", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "tuple", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.tuple", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "tuple", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.tuple", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}]}, "documentation": ["Entity resolution result expressed in terms of the SERF functional model.\n\nThe SERF (Standard Entity Resolution Framework) mathematical model proposes a way of looking\nat entity resolution as if it were the result of applying two types of functions (match\nfunctions and merge functions) over two data sources with unique records (a data set). The model\nbuilds new information records from pairs of existing information records by using a \"domination\"\nrelationship. The \"dominating\" information records take the place of the \"dominated\" information\nrecords until there aren't any more records in the two data sets that can create new \"dominating\"\nrecords. The information records obtained by this process make up a data set that is said to be\nthe entity resolution over the two initial data sources. The SERF ground truth depends on which\n`merge` function is used.\n\nIt was proposed by Omar Benjelloun et al. in the paper\n[Swoosh: a generic approach to entity resolution\\<https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s00778-008-0098-x>][swoosh: a generic approach to entity resolution<https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s00778-008-0098-x>].\n"]}, {"name": "matchescu.adt.entity_resolution_result.EntityResolutionResult.serf", "type": {"name": "list", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.list", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "tuple", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.tuple", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Ground truth is expressed in terms of one or more mathematical models."]}], "exports": []}]}